      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}} and first {{sea-salt-fine}}. Bind with the yolk of the {{eggs}} and the {{water}}. Wrap and chill an hour. Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Roll, line a 23 cm tin, trim and prick. Blind-bake with baking beans for 15 minutes; remove paper and beans and bake another 5 minutes. Brush warm pastry with the reserved egg white to seal.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toast the pecans, mix the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Spread the {{pecans}} on a tray and toast in the oven for 5 minutes until they smell nutty. Cool. In a bowl, whisk the {{golden-syrup}}, {{soft-brown-sugar}}, melted {{unsalted-butter}}, beaten {{eggs}}, {{vanilla-extract}} and second {{sea-salt-fine}} to a smooth thin filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill, bake, cool",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drop the oven to 170°C fan. Scatter the toasted pecans into the pastry case and pour the filling over them. The pecans will float. Bake for 20 minutes, then drop to 150°C and bake for another 20 minutes; the edges should be set, the centre should wobble just slightly. Cool fully in the tin, the filling sets firm as it cools and slices cleanly once the pie is cold.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
